---
const lessons = [
  {
    tag: 'Non-Profit',
    title: 'The Roadmap That Was Never Written',
    body: [
      'A small non-profit asked me to define a five-year technology roadmap. Once we understood how they actually operated, the real issue was operational visibility — reporting, cost allocation and operational data scattered across systems never designed to work together.',
      'Instead of a roadmap, we built a lightweight operational platform that consolidated reporting, retired several expensive systems and gave leadership the visibility they\'d been missing.',
    ],
    punch: "Technology planning wasn't the deliverable. Clarity was.",
  },
  {
    tag: 'Enterprise Software',
    title: 'When Listening to Users Leads You Astray',
    body: [
      'Redesigning a large enterprise application, we assembled over a hundred experienced users. Every suggestion was genuine and would have improved the software they knew. Then we asked a different question: what are you actually trying to accomplish?',
      'The users had unconsciously adapted their work to the software. So we redesigned the workflow around how the business really operated — not the interface.',
    ],
    punch: 'The users understood the software. Our job was to understand the business.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'Telecommunications',
    title: 'Designing the Business Before Changing the Technology',
    body: [
      'A telecoms provider won a major customer and needed to operationalize the service. CRM, billing, accounting, network inventory and the customer portal had all gone live a year earlier — replacing them wasn\'t an option.',
      'We worked across finance, engineering, support, billing and IT to map how information moved, then designed an operating model that let the new customer fit naturally into the existing ecosystem.',
    ],
    punch: 'The biggest improvement wasn\'t new software. It was a better operating model.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section section--paper-2 lessons">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">From Practice</p>
      <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Each of these engagements began with a request for technology. None of them ended there.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lessons__list">
      {lessons.map((l) => (
        <article class="lesson reveal">
          <p class="lesson__tag">{l.tag}</p>
          <h3>{l.title}</h3>
          <div class="lesson__body">
            {l.body.map((p) => <p>{p}</p>)}
          </div>
          <p class="lesson__punch">{l.punch}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="lessons__foot reveal">
      Every one of these stories began with a conversation about technology. Every one ended with a better
      understanding of the business.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .lessons__list { display: grid; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .lesson {
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .lesson__tag {
    color: var(--coral);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .lesson h3 { font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 1.7rem); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lesson__body p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 72ch; }
  .lesson__punch {
    color: var(--teal);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .lessons__foot {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.6vw, 1.4rem);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
